 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.246","title":"[audit][service] Close Buffer after synchronous inner call panic to avoid wedged readiness","description":"src/service/buffer.rs leaves the shared inner service logically reserved if inner.call(req) panics after poll_ready succeeded. PendingGuard releases outer capacity, but the shared inner service can stay wedged, so later poll_ready calls may authorize new work that then hangs forever in WaitingForReady. Harden BufferFuture so a synchronous inner call panic fail-closes the shared buffer before unwinding, add focused regressions proving the service does not wedge, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","notes":"Implemented in src/service/buffer.rs: introduced close_shared_buffer() and now catch synchronous panics from the shared inner service during BufferFuture::poll when calling inner.poll_ready(...) or inner.call(req). On either panic path, the shared buffer is marked closed, waiters are woken, pending capacity is released via PendingGuard, and the panic is resumed so the offending caller still observes the unwind. Added focused regressions inner_poll_ready_panic_closes_buffer_and_future and inner_call_panic_closes_buffer_and_prevents_wedged_readiness. Validation attempted via rch only: (1) rch exec -- cargo test -p asupersync panic_closes_buffer -- --nocapture failed on unrelated current-snapshot compile blockers outside this lane: src/stream/debounce.rs E0502 and src/transport/stream.rs missing SymbolSinkExt import / E0282; (2) rch exec -- cargo fmt --check reports broad pre-existing workspace formatting drift outside this bead, though rustfmt was applied to src/service/buffer.rs locally; (3) rch exec -- cargo check --all-targets and rch exec -- cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings both hit unstable rch worker/build-lock behavior after remote timeout fallback, so no additional lane-specific failures were observed beyond the shared compile frontiers already seen in targeted cargo test. Keeping bead in_progress pending frontier-clear revalidation.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"SwiftBadger","estimated_minutes":90,"created_at":"2026-03-12T05:56:51.682589413Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-12T06:12:39.232499006Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","service"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.246","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-12T05:56:51.682589413Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.247","title":"[compile][stream] Fix Debounce pending-item borrow regression in quiet-period flush","description":"Current HEAD has an incomplete local fix in src/stream/debounce.rs: the quiet-period flush path borrows pending.as_ref() immutably via received_at and then calls pending.take() before that borrow ends, triggering E0502 in cargo check. Restructure the elapsed/flush logic so debounce can move the buffered item without overlapping borrows, preserve the intended semantics of the in-tree take-if-present hardening, and rerun rch-backed library validation to confirm the debounce frontier is cleared while leaving unrelated active frontiers untouched.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"LilacBay","created_at":"2026-03-12T06:02:43.428324990Z","created_by":"LilacBay","updated_at":"2026-03-12T06:02:43.428324990Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","compile","stream"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.247","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-12T06:02:43.428324990Z","created_by":"LilacBay","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.248","title":"[audit][transport] Make SymbolStreamExt futures fail closed after terminal completion","description":"src/transport/stream.rs helper futures lacked terminal completion tracking. This patch makes NextFuture, CollectToSetFuture, and NextWithCancelFuture fail closed with StreamError::PolledAfterCompletion on post-completion repolls, prevents the same future from consuming additional symbols after its first terminal result, adds focused regressions for success/error/exhausted/cancelled paths, and tracks validation state while broader compile frontiers are noisy.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"GreenGlacier","estimated_minutes":90,"created_at":"2026-03-12T06:07:08.992071965Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-12T06:07:08.992071965Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","stream","transport"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.248","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-12T06:07:08.992071965Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
