- `rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-coral-499-test cargo test -p asupersync run_cancelled_before_handler_returns_499 -- --nocapture` also failed due remote `/tmp` exhaustion while compiling unrelated test targets/link steps, not due this web slice.

Conclusion: no code change required for this bead; source + existing tests match the requested behavior.","created_at":"2026-03-10T05:40:22Z"},{"id":2484,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.27","author":"RainyRaven","text":"RainyRaven stale-closure validation pass on 2026-03-10: source still matches the bead exactly (499 mapping present in RequestRegion, CLIENT_CLOSED_REQUEST constant present, focused 499 regressions present), target files are clean, and rch cargo check -p asupersync --lib passed during this pass. No code change required.","created_at":"2026-03-10T18:55:54Z"}]}

